description: From Middle English tarien, taryen (“to vex, harass, cause to hesitate, delay”), from Old English tirgan, tergan, tirian (“to worry, exasperate”).

verbs.description: tarre (third-person singular simple present tarres, present participle tarring, simple past and past participle tarred)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To incite; to provoke; to spur on.

examples: […]  she takes not so much for curing a thousand mortal People, as I have spent in Turpentine and Tarre to keep my Flocklings cleanly in a Spring time.
